PAULDING WIND FARM II LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Paulding Wind Farm II LLC ("Paulding II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Paulding II generating facility ("Paulding II Facility").
The Paulding II Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Paulding County, Ohio. The Paulding II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Ohio Transmission Company, Inc. and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Paulding II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Paulding II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Paulding II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Paulding II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $$359,964.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $29,997.00
